==Old English==
===Etymology===
From a West Germanic variant of Germanic ''*kar-'' (see [[cearu]], [[carian]]).  Cognate with Old Saxon ''carag'', Old High German ''[[karag]]''
===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ʧæaɹɪj/

===Adjective===
'''ċeariġ'''
# [[careful]], [[wary]]
# [[sad]], [[sorrowful]], [[anxious]]

